<!-- carbon badge (DELICIOUS IN DUNGEON's organic-form embodiment): delicious-in-dungeon.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** DELICIOUS IN DUNGEON — an entertainment sphere — an anime-world

**what —** A party loses their swordsman's sister to a dragon deep in a labyrinth, and they're broke. So they go back in — and, to survive without supplies, they start cooking and eating the monsters. What sounds like a gag becomes a meticulous, warm study of an ecosystem, a found family, and what it means to live off a world rather than just conquer it.

**where —** an anime-world catalogued into UD0  Framework inputs: the cast; the world; the conceit; the theme  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** A party loses their swordsman's sister to a dragon deep in a labyrinth, and they're broke. So they go back in — and, to survive without supplies, they start cooking and eating the monsters. What sounds like a gag becomes a meticulous, warm study of an ecosystem, a found family, and what it means to live off a world rather than just conquer it.

